The paper also presents deterministic and randomized algorithms for the problem, which falls under the category of algorithm design and analysis (cs.AL). The paper also uses game-theoretic concepts to analyze the competitive ratio of the algorithms, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also presents lower and upper bounds for the problem, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper also discusses the performance of the algorithms in terms of their competitive ratio, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
